Hello! I'm Beau, a junior low-level systems developer and retro enthusiast. Computers were much more simple some decades ago, and I spend much of my development time trying to create modern systems that don't isolate you from each and every instruction your CPU chews through. This area fascinates me for two reasons: it helps me understand how computers function on a deeper level than programming courses could ever hope to teach, but also because I simply adore computers, and always have.

I'm not a frontend developer, so this webiste isn't some flashy design project, but you can reach these pages from 6 different internet protocols, all of which I have implemented from scratch in Nim.

