# My skills

I am a self-taught software developer, and have been for 6 years. I got started in the space as most do, by learning Python. I still use Python often as it is a highly expressive language that makes it easy to implement things fast. However, in the time since I began learning programming, I became increasingly curious about how exactly my computer executes the code I write. This has since led me down a rabbit-hole of learning C, Nim (my favorite programming language) and eventually Assembly (albeit for the 6502 architecture). This definitely helped me understand the workings of my computer, but a functioning machine is more than just a CPU. So, next, I began a project where I rebuilt all the layers of abstraction inside modern computers - this is what became the Ozpex 128, where I have designed, and implemented an emulator, for an entirely custom computer architecture and written a BIOS, bootloader, kernel, filesystem and interpreted language for.

